The paper discusses the use of deep learning models for question answering, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses pre-training and fine-tuning of models, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The comparison of different pre-training models involves evaluating their performance, which is a task commonly associated with machine learning and statistical analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well. The paper also involves information retrieval and text classification, which are topics covered in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories.
